TITLE: Configuring Markdown Extensions for GitHub-like Experience in Python
DESCRIPTION: This Python code snippet demonstrates how to override default configuration options for Markdown extensions when using the 'pymdownx.github' extension. By nesting sub-extension settings under their specific keys, users can finely tune the behavior (e.g., enabling the 'subscript' option for the 'pymdownx.tilde' extension). A dictionary named 'extension_configs' is used, mapping extension names to their configuration dictionaries. Inputs are Python dict objects specifying extension parameters; outputs are the applied runtime configuration. The approach assumes use within a Python Markdown environment with proper extension packages installed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/pymdown-extensions/docs/src/markdown/extensions/github.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Python
CODE:
```
extension_configs = {
    'pymdownx.github': {
        'pymdownx.tilde': {
            'subscript': True
        }
    }
}
```

