TITLE: Enabling MagicLink in Python Markdown - Python
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use Python's markdown library in conjunction with the 'pymdownx.magiclink' extension to automatically convert URLs in text into clickable hyperlinks in the generated HTML. The example requires Python and the markdown package with the pymdown-extensions installed. It shows importing the library, preparing the input text, processing it, and the expected HTML output string.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/pymdown-extensions/docs/src/markdown/index.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: pycon3
CODE:
```
>>> import markdown
>>> text = "A link https://google.com"
>>> html = markdown.markdown(text, ['pymdownx.magiclink'])
'<p>A link <a href="https://google.com">https://google.com</a></p>'
```

