TITLE: Complex Action Example with Logging in CloudScripting (YAML)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates a more complex use of actions, including file creation, appending content, and logging IP addresses of compute nodes. It showcases how to combine multiple actions and use placeholders for node information.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/docs/creating-manifest/actions.md#2025-04-23_snippet_74

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
type: update
name: Action Example

onInstall:
  - createFile [cp]: ${SERVER_WEBROOT}/greeting.txt
  - greeting
  - greeting
  - log:
      message: ${nodes.cp[0].address}
  - log:
      message: ${nodes.cp[1].address}

actions:
  greeting:
    appendFile [cp]:
      path: ${SERVER_WEBROOT}/greeting.txt
      body: Hello World!
  log:
    appendFile [cp]:
      path: ${SERVER_WEBROOT}/greeting.txt
      body: ${this.message}
```

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "update",
  "name": "Action Example",
  "onInstall": [
    {
      "createFile [cp]": "${SERVER_WEBROOT}/greeting.txt"
    },
    "greeting",
    "greeting",
    {
      "log": {
        "message": "${nodes.cp[0].address}"
      }
    },
    {
      "log": {
        "message": "${nodes.cp[1].address}"
      }
    }
  ],
  "actions": {
    "greeting": {
      "appendFile [cp]": {
        "path": "${SERVER_WEBROOT}/greeting.txt",
        "body": "Hello World!"
      }
    },
    "log": {
      "appendFile [cp]": {
