TITLE: Using 'else' Conditional Operator in Cloud Scripting (YAML and JSON)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the 'else' conditional operator in Cloud Scripting, including nested conditions and various test cases.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/docs/creating-manifest/conditions-and-iterations.md#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
type: install
name: '[CS:Conditions] - action "else"'

globals:
  a: 1
  b: 2

onInstall:
- log: "-- else condition test --"
- if (false):
    assert: false
- else:
    assert: true
- if (globals.a === 1):
    assert: true
- else:
    assert: false

- log: "-- nested conditions test --"
- if ('${globals.b}' === '2'):
    if (false):
      assert: false
- else:
    assert: false

- log: "-- conditions position test --"
- if (false):
    assert: true
- log: test
- else:
    assert: false

- log: "-- invalid condition test --"
- if ( ):
    assert: false
- else:
    assert: false
```

