TITLE: Add-on Installation Events Subscription Example in YAML and JSON
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to subscribe to onBeforeInstallAddon and onAfterInstallAddon events which are triggered before and after add-on installation. This example filters events by node group and add-on ID, then logs relevant information from the event parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/docs/creating-manifest/events.md#2025-04-23_snippet_30

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
type: update  
name: Test Add-on Events Subscription  

onBeforeInstallAddon [nodeGroup:cp, id:myaddon]:  
  log: add-on  
  ID: ${event.params.id}  

onAfterInstallAddon [nodeGroup:cp, id:myaddon]:  
  log: add-on  
  unique name: ${event.response.uniqueName}   
```

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
  {
  "type": "update",
  "name": "Test Add-on Events Subscription",
  "onBeforeInstallAddon [nodeGroup:cp, id:myaddon": {
    "log": "add-on",
    "ID": "${event.params.id}"
  },
  "onAfterInstallAddon [nodeGroup:cp, id:myaddon]": {
    "log": "add-on",
    "unique name": "${event.response.uniqueName}"
  }
}  
```

