TITLE: Synchronous Environment Installation in Virtuozzo CloudScripting
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating synchronous installation where environments are installed sequentially. This approach is used when one environment depends on another. The example creates two different environments with Apache and Nginx respectively.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/docs/creating-manifest/actions.md#2025-04-23_snippet_61

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
type: update
name: Install action

onInstall:
  - install:
    	type: install
    	region: dev1
    	envName: env-${fn.random}
    	name: test1
    	nodes:
      	nodeType: apache2
      	cloudlets: 16
    	onInstall: 
      	log: install test1
  - install:
    	type: install
    	region: dev2
    	envName: env-${fn.random}
    	name: test2
    	nodes:
      	nodeType: nginx
      	cloudlets: 16
    	onInstall: 
      	log: install test2
```

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "update",
  "name": "Install action",
  "onInstall": [
    {
      "install": {
        "type": "install",
        "region": "dev1",
        "envName": "env-${fn.random}",
        "name": "test1",
        "nodes": {
          "nodeType": "apache2",
          "cloudlets": 16
        },
        "onInstall": {
          "log": "install test1"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "install": {
        "type": "install",
        "region": "dev2",
        "envName": "env-${fn.random}",
        "name": "test2",
        "nodes": {
          "nodeType": "nginx",
          "cloudlets": 16
        },
        "onInstall": {
          "log": "install test2"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

