TITLE: Processing Compute Nodes with Mirror Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Script that identifies compute nodes and configures mirror server IPs for each node. Returns a result object with procedure calls for node processing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/docs/examples/operation-examples.md#2025-04-23_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var softNodeProperties = softNode.getProperties();

if (NODE_MISSION_COMPUTE.equals(softNodeProperties.getNodeGroup())) {
    computeNodes.push(softNode);
}

callArgs = [];
for (var i = 0, n = computeNodes.length; i < n; i += 1) {
    var mirrorServerIp = computeNodes[(i + 1) === computeNodes.length ? 0 : i + 1].getAddress();

    callArgs.push({
        procedure : PROCEDURE_PROCESS_NODE,
        params : {
            nodeId : computeNodes[i].getId(),
            mirrorServerIp : mirrorServerIp
        }
    });

} 

return {
    result : 0,
    onAfterReturn : {
        call : callArgs
    }
};
```

