TITLE: Configuring Nginx Worker Auto-scaling
DESCRIPTION: Implements automatic adjustment of Nginx worker processes to match CPU core count. The configuration triggers on initial installation and whenever the cloudlet count changes for nginx nodes. Uses sed command to modify nginx.conf and reload the service.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/docs/examples/vertical-scaling.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "update",
  "name": "Nginx Balancer Vertical Scaling",
  "onInstall": "adjustWorkersCount",
  "onAfterSetCloudletCount[nodeType:nginx]": "adjustWorkersCount",
  "actions": {
    "adjustWorkersCount": {
      "execmCmd [nodeType:nginx]": "sed -i \"s|worker_processes.*|worker_processes $(cat /proc/cpuinfo | grep -c 'cpu cores');|g\" /etc/nginx/nginx.conf; sudo /etc/init.d/nginx reload 2>&1"
    }
  }
}
```

