TITLE: Removing ManageCat Configuration from Apache Tomcat in Bash
DESCRIPTION: This Bash script removes ManageCat-related configurations from Tomcat's catalina.properties file. It's used during the uninstallation process of ManageCat.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/docs/examples/add-ons.md#2025-04-23_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
[ -f /opt/tomcat/conf/catalina.properties ] && sed -i "/com.managecat/d"  /opt/tomcat/conf/catalina.properties 2>>/dev/null 1>>/dev/null
if [ -d /opt/tomcat8 ]; then [ -f /opt/tomcat8/conf/catalina.properties ] && sed -i "/com.managecat/d" /opt/tomcat8/conf/catalina.properties; fi
```

