TITLE: Implementing Elif Conditional Logic in Cloud Scripts
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the use of elif conditions in Cloud Scripts with both positive and negative test cases. Shows how elif statements are evaluated in sequence and how they interact with if/else blocks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/docs/creating-manifest/conditions-and-iterations.md#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
type: install
name: '[CS:Conditions] - action "elif"'

globals:
  a: 1
  b: 2

onInstall:
- log: "-- elif positive test  --"
- if (globals.a == 2):
    assert: false
- elif (globals.a == 3):
    assert: false
- elif (globals.a == 1):
    assert: true
- elif (globals.a == 1):
    assert: false
- elif (globals.b == 2):
    assert: false
- else:
    assert: false

- log: "-- elif negative test  --"
- if (globals.a == 1):
    assert: true
- elif (globals.a == 1):
    assert: false
- elif (globals.a == 1):
    assert: false
```

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "install",
  "name": "[CS:Conditions] - action 'elif'",
  "globals": {
    "a": 1,
    "b": 2
  },
  "onInstall": [
    {
      "log": "-- elif positive test  --"
    },
    {
      "if (globals.a == 2)": {
        "assert": false
      }
    },
    {
      "elif (globals.a == 3)": {
        "assert": false
      }
    },
    {
      "elif (globals.a == 1)": {
        "assert": true
      }
    },
    {
      "elif (globals.a == 1)": {
        "assert": false
      }
    },
    {
      "elif (globals.b == 2)": {
        "assert": false
      }
    },
    {
      "else": {
        "assert": false
      }
    },
    {
      "log": "-- elif negative test  --"
    },
    {
      "if (globals.a == 1)": {
        "assert": true
      }
    },
    {
      "elif (globals.a == 1)": {
        "assert": false
      }
    },
    {
      "elif (globals.a == 1)": {
        "assert": false
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

