TITLE: Configuring MathJax Behavior and TeX Input/Output (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet configures the MathJax library using `MathJax.Hub.Config`. It sets up TeX as an input format, HTML-CSS and NativeMML as output formats, enables MathMenu and MathZoom extensions, defines TeX-specific rendering options like right-aligned tags, automatic AMS equation numbering, and line width. It also sets the display alignment to the left and suppresses processing messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/pymdown-extensions/docs/src/markdown/_snippets/mathjax.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
<script type="text/x-mathjax-config">
MathJax.Hub.Config({
    config: ["MMLorHTML.js"],
    jax: ["input/TeX", "output/HTML-CSS", "output/NativeMML"],
    extensions: ["MathMenu.js", "MathZoom.js"],
    TeX: {
        TagSide: "right",
        TagIndent: ".8em",
        MultLineWidth: "85%",
        equationNumbers: {
            autoNumber: "AMS",
        }
    },
    displayAlign: 'left',
    showProcessingMessages: false,
