TITLE: Implementing a Custom Preprocessor in Python-Markdown
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to create a custom Preprocessor by inheriting from the markdown.preprocessors.Preprocessor class and implementing the run method, which processes the source text line by line before it's passed to the Markdown parser.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/markdown/docs/extensions/api.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
from markdown.preprocessors import Preprocessor

class MyPreprocessor(Preprocessor):
    def run(self, lines):
        new_lines = []
        for line in lines:
            m = MYREGEX.match(line)
            if m:
                # do stuff
            else:
                new_lines.append(line)
        return new_lines
```

