TITLE: Extending Markdown with a Custom Inline Pattern - Python
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to extend the Markdown parser in Python by defining a custom Extension class and overriding the extendMarkdown method. This code adds a new inline pattern (here, 'mypattern') to the Markdown parsing pipeline before the 'references' pattern. Dependencies include the markdown.extensions.Extension base class and a user-defined MyPattern class to implement the pattern logic. 'md' is the Markdown instance to be extended; 'md_globals' provides global module context. The method should only manipulate the processing pipeline and properly insert patterns.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/markdown/docs/extensions/api.md#2025-04-23_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
from markdown.extensions import Extension

class MyExtension(Extension):
    def extendMarkdown(self, md, md_globals):
        # Insert instance of 'mypattern' before 'references' pattern
        md.inlinePatterns.add('mypattern', MyPattern(md), '<references')
```

