TITLE: Generating Navigation Menu in MkDocs Theme - Django (Jinja2)
DESCRIPTION: Provides a Jinja2 template for rendering nested navigation menus in MkDocs themes by iterating over the 'nav' object. It supports active state highlighting and recursion for child pages, allowing for multi-level navigation structures within the documentation layout. Relies on the presence of the 'nav' variable and its 'children', 'title', 'active', and 'url' attributes. Renders HTML unordered lists based on navigation hierarchy, and outputs a dynamic navigation menu reflecting the structure defined in mkdocs.yml.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/mkdocs/docs/user-guide/custom-themes.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: django
CODE:
```
{% if nav|length>1 %}\n    <ul>\n    {% for nav_item in nav %}\n        {% if nav_item.children %}\n            <li>{{ nav_item.title }}\n                <ul>\n                {% for nav_item in nav_item.children %}\n                    <li class="{% if nav_item.active%}current{%endif%}">\n                        <a href="{{ nav_item.url }}">{{ nav_item.title }}</a>\n                    </li>\n                {% endfor %}\n                </ul>\n            </li>\n        {% else %}\n            <li class="{% if nav_item.active%}current{%endif%}">\n                <a href="{{ nav_item.url }}">{{ nav_item.title }}</a>\n            </li>\n        {% endif %}\n    {% endfor %}\n    </ul>\n{% endif %}
```

