TITLE: Providing CSS Polyfill for Details/Summary - CSS
DESCRIPTION: This CSS snippet provides a basic styling and polyfill for consistent rendering of <details>/<summary> tags in browsers. It handles display issues, provides open/closed state indicators with Unicode arrows, disables the default marker, and uses the 'no-details' class to simulate open/close in unsupported browsers. Depends on being loaded in browsers as part of the page; works in conjunction with the JavaScript polyfill. Inputs are HTML with <details> blocks; outputs are styled collapsible sections. Limitations include that more complex features may require a more complete polyfill.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/pymdown-extensions/docs/src/markdown/extensions/details.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: css
CODE:
```
details {
  display: block;
}

details[open] > summary::before {
  content: "\25BC";
}

details summary {
  display: block;
  cursor: pointer;
}

details summary:focus {
  outline: none;
}

details summary::before {
  content: "\25B6";
  padding-right: 0.5em;
}

details summary::-webkit-details-marker {
  display: none;
}

/* Attach the "no-details" class to details tags
   in browsers that do not support them to get
   open/show functionality. */
details.no-details:not([open]) > * {
  display: none;
}

details.no-details:not([open]) summary {
  display: block;
}
```

