TITLE: Stopping Events with Custom Messages in CloudScripting (YAML)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to use the stopEvent action to prevent a node restart based on a setting. It demonstrates conditional execution and displaying custom warning messages in the CloudScripting interface.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/docs/creating-manifest/actions.md#2025-04-23_snippet_75

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
type: install
name: stopEvent Test

settings:
  fields:
    type: checkbox
    name: restart
    caption: App Server Restart Allow
    default: true

nodes:
  - nodeType: apache2
    nodeGroup: cp
    count: 1
    cloudlets: 4
  - nodeType: nginx
    nodeGroup: bl
    count: 1
    cloudlets: 4

onBeforeRestartNode[cp]:
  if ( ${settings.restart} == false ):
      stopEvent:
        type: warning
        message: Restart is prohibited. 
```

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "install",
  "name": "stopEvent Test",
  "settings": {
    "fields": {
      "type": "checkbox",
      "name": "restart",
      "caption": "App Server Restart Allow",
      "default": true
    }
  },
  "nodes": [
    {
      "nodeType": "apache2",
      "nodeGroup": "cp",
      "count": 1,
      "cloudlets": 4
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "nginx",
      "nodeGroup": "bl",
      "count": 1,
      "cloudlets": 4
    }
  ],
  "onBeforeRestartNode[cp]": {
    "if ( ${settings.restart} == false )": {
      "stopEvent": {
        "type": "warning",
        "message": "Restart is prohibited."
      }
    }
  }
}
```

