TITLE: Configuring MathJax for Generic Arithmatex Output using JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Presents a JavaScript configuration for MathJax tailored for Arithmatex's 'generic' output mode. It explicitly enables and configures the `tex2jax` extension to process elements with the `arithmatex` class, looking for `\\(...\\)` and `\\[...\\]` delimiters. It ignores other classes and enables processing of LaTeX environments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/pymdown-extensions/docs/src/markdown/extensions/arithmatex.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
MathJax.Hub.Config({
  config: ["MMLorHTML.js"],
  extensions: ["tex2jax.js"],
  jax: ["input/TeX", "output/HTML-CSS", "output/NativeMML"],
  tex2jax: {
    inlineMath: [ ["\\(","\\)"] ],
    displayMath: [ ["\\[","\\]"] ],
    processEscapes: true,
    processEnvironments: true,
    ignoreClass: ".*|",
    processClass: "arithmatex"
  },
});
```

