TITLE: Initializing MkDocs Theme Layout with Jinja2 - Django (Jinja2)
DESCRIPTION: Defines the core structure of the main.html template for a MkDocs custom theme using Jinja2 templating syntax. It conditionally renders the page title, includes the site name, and inserts the rendered content for each documentation page using {{ content }}. No external dependencies other than MkDocs and Jinja2 are required. Inputs are template variables (page_title, site_name, content), and output is a valid HTML page. This snippet is intended as the minimal starting point for a new MkDocs theme.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/mkdocs/docs/user-guide/custom-themes.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: django
CODE:
```
<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n  <head>\n    <title>{% if page_title %}{{ page_title }} - {% endif %}{{ site_name }}</title>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    {{ content }}\n  </body>\n</html>
```

