TITLE: Custom SSH Wrapper for Git Environment - Shell
DESCRIPTION: Provides a shell script for use as a GIT_SSH or GIT_SSH_COMMAND target, which wraps execution of ssh with customized parameters, e.g., specifying an identity file and disabling host key checks. The script must be executable and used to control git's connection behavior, especially as a daemon. Parameters and dependencies include a valid user-supplied private key path, and placement on the file system accessible to the repo.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/GitPython/doc/source/tutorial.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_40

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
#!/bin/sh
ID_RSA=/var/lib/openshift/5562b947ecdd5ce939000038/app-deployments/id_rsa
exec /usr/bin/ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -i $ID_RSA "$@"

```

