TITLE: Documenting onBeforeLinkNode Event in Markdown
DESCRIPTION: Describes the onBeforeLinkNode event triggered before linking nodes to apply configurations to IP addresses. It specifies compatibility and details event placeholders.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/docs/creating-manifest/events.md#2025-04-23_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
### onBeforeLinkNode

The event is executed before linking nodes to apply configurations to IP addresses. It is compatible only with *compute* and *balancer* node groups and excludes Docker nodes.

**Event Placeholders:**

- `${event.params.}`:
    - `parentNodes` - node identifiers for linking
    - `session` - current user session
    - `appid` - environment unique appid
    - `childNodes` - node identifiers for linking with parent nodes
    - `env` - environment short name
- `${event.response.}`- parameters are absent
```

