TITLE: Creating HTML Table with ElementTree
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to construct an HTML table using ElementTree, including setting attributes and adding formatted content.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/markdown/docs/extensions/api.md#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
table = etree.Element("table")
table.set("cellpadding", "2")                      # Set cellpadding to 2
tr = etree.SubElement(table, "tr")                 # Add child tr to table
td1 = etree.SubElement(tr, "td")                   # Add child td1 to tr
td1.text = markdown.util.AtomicString("Cell content") # Add plain text content
td2 = etree.SubElement(tr, "td")                   # Add second td to tr
td2.text = "*text* with **inline** formatting."    # Add markup text
table.tail = "Text after table"                    # Add text after table
```

