TITLE: Rendering Obfuscated Email as Mailto Link with JavaScript - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet deobfuscates an email address and dynamically updates a span element\'s content with a mailto link. It relies on manipulating strings: first sorts the characters of an obfuscated string, then reconstructs the actual email using a mapping. Dependencies include the HTML element with an id of \"e116142240\". Key parameters include the variables a (obfuscated string), c (encryption key), and the output is the deobfuscated email rendered to the page. The script assumes the existence of the target span and does not perform validation or error handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/markdown/tests/misc/escaped_chars_in_js.txt#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
