TITLE: Initializing Regular Expression Pattern Matcher in Python
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines the __init__ method for a class that handles regular expression pattern matching. It compiles a regular expression with the given pattern, allowing for multi-line matching. The class also provides a method to retrieve the compiled regular expression object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/markdown/tests/extensions/codehilite.txt#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def __init__ (self, pattern) :
    self.pattern = pattern
    self.compiled_re = re.compile("^(.*)%s(.*)$" % pattern, re.DOTALL)

def getCompiledRegExp (self) :
    return self.compiled_re
```

