TITLE: Configuring MathJax using JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet configures the MathJax library. It sets up input (TeX) and output (HTML-CSS, NativeMML) formats, loads necessary extensions (tex2jax, MathMenu, MathZoom), defines delimiters for inline (`\\( ... \\)`) and display (`\\[ ... \\]`) math, sets display alignment, and hides processing messages. This configuration needs to be included in an HTML file before the MathJax library itself.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/pymdown-extensions/tests/extensions/arithmatex/arithmatex (generic).txt#2025-04-23_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
<script type="text/x-mathjax-config">
MathJax.Hub.Config({
    config: ["MMLorHTML.js"],
    jax: ["input/TeX", "output/HTML-CSS", "output/NativeMML"],
    extensions: ["tex2jax.js", "MathMenu.js", "MathZoom.js"],
    tex2jax: {
        inlineMath: [ ["\\(","\\)"] ],
        displayMath: [ ["\[","\]"] ]
    },
    displayAlign: 'left',
    showProcessingMessages: false,
    messageStyle: 'none'
});
</script>
```

