TITLE: Creating a Custom Emphasis Pattern for Python-Markdown
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to implement a custom inline pattern for emphasis by inheriting from the Pattern class and implementing the handleMatch method to generate an 'em' element in the ElementTree.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/markdown/docs/extensions/api.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
from markdown.inlinepatterns import Pattern
from markdown.util import etree

class EmphasisPattern(Pattern):
    def handleMatch(self, m):
        el = etree.Element('em')
        el.text = m.group(3)
        return el
```

