DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the necessity of registering a Markdown extension to properly reset internal state when the parent Markdown instance is reset. Here, after invoking md.registerExtension(self), the extension's reset() method will also be called automatically. Required dependency is a subclass of markdown.extensions.Extension, and registration must take place inside extendMarkdown. Input is the extension instance, output is registration and proper callback on reset.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/markdown/docs/extensions/api.md#2025-04-23_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def extendMarkdown(self, md, md_globals):
    md.registerExtension(self)
    # insert processors and patterns here
```

