TITLE: Configuring PyMdown "extra" Extension in Python
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to set configuration options for individual extensions included through PyMdown Extensions' 'extra' extension. The dictionary 'extension_configs' is used to specify configuration for sub-extensions, such as setting the 'BACKLINK_TEXT' in 'markdown.extensions.footnotes' to 'link'. Requires Python Markdown and PyMdown Extensions installed and referenced in the project. The configuration expects sub-extension keys to map to dictionaries of option-value pairs, customizing the Markdown parser's behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/pymdown-extensions/docs/src/markdown/extensions/extra.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: py3
CODE:
```
extension_configs = {
    'pymdownx.extra': {
        'markdown.extensions.footnotes': {
            'BACKLINK_TEXT': 'link'
        }
    }
}
```

