TITLE: Configuring and Loading MathJax for LaTeX Rendering - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet initializes MathJax by configuring its input and output processors, sets various extensions (such as MathMenu and MathZoom), and modifies message/processing display options. The script block of type 'text/x-mathjax-config' ensures MathJax is configured before loading. The subsequent 'script src' tag dynamically loads the MathJax library from a CDN. Dependencies: internet access to the specified CDN URL, HTML DOM environment. No input parameters are required; output is the enabled rendering of LaTeX markup to math notation in the HTML document. Limitations: Configuration applies globally to the page, and changes need a reload to take effect.
SOURCE: https://github.com/virtuozzo/cloudscripting-docs/blob/master/3rdparty/pymdown-extensions/tests/extensions/arithmatex/arithmatex (disable).txt#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
<script type="text/x-mathjax-config">\nMathJax.Hub.Config({\n    config: [\"MMLorHTML.js\"],\n    jax: [\"input/TeX\", \"output/HTML-CSS\", \"output/NativeMML\"],\n    extensions: [\"MathMenu.js\", \"MathZoom.js\"],\n    displayAlign: 'left',\n    showProcessingMessages: false,\n    messageStyle: 'none'\n});\n</script>\n<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/mathjax/2.7.0/MathJax.js"></script>
```

